article.headline: (18) DEPAUL 92, HOLY CROSS 49
article.story:
CHICAGO (AP) -- Khara Smith scored 19 points and Allie Quigley
added 18 to lead No. 19 DePaul to a 92-49 victory over Holy Cross
on Sunday night.

Smith grabbed 14 rebounds and Jenni Dant and Caprice Smith each
added 10 points to give the Blue Demons their fifth straight win.

DePaul (11-2) led 47-27 at the break and increased its lead in
the second half by shooting 7-of-10 from 3-point range.

Holy Cross (5-7) shot just 32.1 percent from the field. Lisa
Andrews and Maggie Fontana led the Crusaders with 10 points each.
